    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "x-api-key",
              "value": "={{ $env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}"
            },
            {
              "name": "anthropic-version",
              "value": "2023-06-01"
            },
            {
              "name": "anthropic-beta",
              "value": "mcp-client-1.0"
            }
          ]
        },
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={{ JSON.stringify({ model: 'claude-sonnet-4-6', max_tokens: 4096, mcp_servers: [{ url: 'https://memory.fl1.it/mcp', type: 'url', authorization_token: $env.CODEGRAPH_AUTH_TOKEN }], system: 'Sei @skill-syncer. Esegui una skill sync completa:\\n1. Chiama memory_search({ query: \"skill:\", limit: 100 }) per trovare memorie con tag skill:XXX\\n2. Raggruppa per tag skill:XXX, considera solo quelle degli ultimi 30 giorni (campo created_at)\\n3. Per ogni skill con \u2265 3 memorie nuove:\\n   a. skill_read({ name: \"X\" })\\n   b. Analizza cosa manca nella skill rispetto alle memorie\\n   c. Genera proposta concisa (solo aggiunte/modifiche)\\n   d. Salva con memory_add({ type: \"Todo\", context: \"Skill update proposal for X\", problem: \"Skill outdated vs recent learnings\", solution: LA_PROPOSTA_COMPLETA, reason: \"N new memories with tag skill:X\", tags: [\"skill-proposal\", \"skill:X\", \"status:pending\"], confidence: 8, importance: 7, project: \"skillbrain\" })\\n4. IMPORTANTE: alla fine rispondi SOLO con questo JSON: {\"proposals\":[{\"skill\":\"NAME\",\"memories\":N}]}\\nSe nessuna skill ha \u22653 memorie: {\"proposals\":[]}', messages: [{ role: 'user', content: 'Run skill sync now' }] }) }}"
      },
      "id": "node-api-sync",
      "name": "Anthropic \u2014 Run Sync",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4,
      "position": [
        900,
        180
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const response = $input.first().json;\nconst textBlock = response.content?.find(b => b.type === 'text');\nconst text = textBlock?.text || '';\nconst match = text.match(/\\{[\\s\\S]*\"proposals\"[\\s\\S]*\\}/);\nlet proposals = [];\ntry { proposals = match ? JSON.parse(match[0]).proposals : []; } catch(e) {}\nreturn [{ json: { proposals, count: proposals.length } }];"
      },
      "id": "node-parse-sync",
      "name": "Parse Proposals",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        1120,
        180
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": true,
            "leftValue": "",
            "typeValidation": "strict"
          },
          "conditions": [
            {
              "id": "c4",
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.count }}",
              "rightValue": 0,
              "operator": {
                "type": "number",
                "operation": "gt"
